SIMPLE: turbo
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: turbo
<hw>tur"bo</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>turbo</ets>,
<ets>-inis</ets>, a top. See <er>Turbine</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Any one of numerous marine gastropods of the genus <gen>Turbo</gen>
or family <fam>Turbinidae</fam>, usually having a turbinate shell,
pearly on the inside, and a calcareous operculum.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>turbo-</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: turbo-
<hw>tur"bo-</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Sontaining or using a
turbine; -- a combining form; <as>as, <ex>turbo</ex>jet</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Turbogenerator</ent>⟦br⟧
